Subject: Methods to Introduce GRID for Boots Project

All,

As discussed on the call we have a number of options to integrate pattern
based authentication into Boots.

Option 1

We provide a .net based authentication API which can be used to integrate
your authentication page for in-house apps. An example of the .NET API is
attached. This would require some internal development at Boots and amending
existing applications.


Option 2

Java based web integration. We also have the ability to embed a small piece
of java into a page to generate the grid got authentication The java script
required  would look something like below

<TD align="right">
<input id="BSID_challengeButton" type="button" name="grid" value='Get Grid'
title="Get Grid" 
onClick="getChallenge(document.getElementById('UID').value)">

                   <INPUT type="submit" value="Log On" id="SubmitCreds"
name="SubmitCreds" >
<div id="challengeImageDiv" style="visibility:hidden; display:none;"><img
id="challengeImage" src=""/></div>
                 </TD>

<SCRIPT LANGUAGE='JavaScript'>
<!--


//------GrIDsure beginning-----


var BlackShieldServerLocation =
"https://ss.safenet-inc.com/blackshieldss/O/ANSX25AOW8/index.aspx?"

function getChallenge(userName){
    var challengeImg = document.getElementById("challengeImage");
    challengeImg.src = BlackShieldServerLocation +
"?getChallengeImage=true&userName=" + userName + "&noCache=" + new
Date().toString();
    var challengeDiv = document.getElementById("challengeImageDiv");
    challengeDiv.style.display="block";
    challengeDiv.style.visibility="visible";
}

//--------GrIDsure end------

Option 3

Use of a Gateway or Proxy to provide grid authentication prior to accessing
the web app.
 
We have the ability to integrate the grid into other technologies such as
Juniper Appliances and Microsoft gateway technologies such as UAG with an
example  attached also.


I have also include an example .login page with the authentication and grid
token attached which should provide you with a starting point for this
project.




Kind Regards

